To do binary search, sometimes I see people use
```
mid = (low + high) / 2;
```
Sometimes I see
```
mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
```

*mid* will at most diff 1. What is the difference between these two approaches?

Here is my code, it works with "low + (high - low)" but TLE with (low + high) / 2.

```
    public int guessNumber(int n) {
        int low = 1, high = n;
        int result = low + (high - low) / 2;
        int guess = 0;
        while ((guess = (guess(result))) != 0) {
            if (guess > 0) {
                low = result + 1;
            } else {
                high = result - 1;
            }
            result = low + (high - low) / 2;
        }
        return result;
    }
```

