using (start + end)/2 instead of mid= start+(end-start)/2 will lead to overflows(beg + end > Integer.MAX_VALUE) or change all the int variable to the long variables 



**Extended Explanation**
the variable mid exceeds the limit and becomes negative:- int can take values upto -2^31 to (2^31)-1
ie, 01111111111111111111111111111111 to 10000000000000000000000000000000
so if we add 1 to 01111111111111111111111111111111 we get 010000000000000000000000000000000 but since our int can't store all the bits
it just stores 10000000000000000000000000000000 and that is negative so our binary search just keeps oscillating and ends up in an infinite loop

