# Intuition
As per given 3 conditions we can, return 1, -1, or the guessed number.

# Approach
1. We will have l (lower / left side number) and r (right side / higher number), by default l =1, r = n (as per given constraint: 1 <= pick <= n).
2. Loop through while l <= 2.
3. Take m = l + (r-1)/2.
4. if(guess(m) == 0), return m; if(guess(m) < 0>), return r = m-1; else l = m+1;
5. Return 0 at the end.

